msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:10
msgid "Goals"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:12
msgid "**A Code of Conduct should:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:13
msgid "Be easy to read (You shouldn't need a law degree to understand it.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:14
msgid "Be easy to find"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:15
msgid "Explain how to report problematic or unethical behavior"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:16
msgid "Explain the consequences of violating Code of Conduct provisions"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:17
msgid "Include timelines/deadlines for enforcement action that will be taken"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:19
msgid "Additional ways to support and implement your Code of Conduct:"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:20
msgid "Include FAQs"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:21
msgid "Encourage positive behavior (don't just discourage negative behavior)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:22
msgid ""
"Have a \"quick\" version and a \"less quick\" version (e.g. "
"[JSConf](http://jsconf.com/codeofconduct.html))"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:24
msgid "Awareness"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:26
msgid ""
"Make sure that **everyone involved in your conference/event** is aware "
"that the Code of Conduct applies to them: that not only includes "
"participants, but also speakers, sponsors, committee members etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:28
msgid ""
"üçé Tick box at registration that confirms that the participant has read "
"the Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:29
msgid "A pop-up with a short version may also be a good idea."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:30
msgid ""
"Provide a link to the full (\"less quick\") version of the Code of "
"Conduct, hosted on its own page."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:31
msgid "üçé Include a copy of the Code of Conduct in the sponsor packet"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:32
msgid ""
"üçé Mention that the Code of Conduct applies to the speakers in the speaker"
" guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:33
msgid ""
"üçé Ensure that the Code of Conduct is **easily** accessible on the "
"conference website"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:34
msgid ""
"Should be in main navigation or in the footer (footer is a known pattern,"
" near privacy policy / terms of service)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:35
msgid ""
"Implement additional web-based highlights of the CoC via loading pages, "
"pop-ups, screen savers, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:36
msgid ""
"üçé Include a short version of the Code of Conduct on the printed schedule "
"as a reminder"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:37
msgid ""
"üçé Mention the Code of Conduct in the welcome talk and at the start of "
"every day, including who to contact if there is a problem/violation"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:38
msgid ""
"üçé Place Code of Conduct reminders on tables at lunch and also signs in "
"rooms reminding people during the day"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:39
msgid ""
"üçé Create a large banner sign at key entrances on the Code of Conduct as a"
" reminder."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:40
msgid ""
"If you send out daily event e-mails, include an item on &quot;Seeing or "
"experiencing something that makes you uncomfortable&quot;"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:41
msgid ""
"&quot;Remember that you can always speak to one of our ombudspersons "
"about any matter of concern, no matter how small.&quot;"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:42
msgid ""
"Include short blurbs about the Code of Conduct during breaks (e.g. during"
" slide breaks), on websites, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:43
msgid "Consider a visual &quot;workflow&quot; of Code of Conduct violation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:44
msgid "Report -&gt; Action -&gt; Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:45
msgid "Make it clear what the consequences or resolutions of a violation are"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:47
msgid "Reporting"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:49
msgid ""
"Ensure confidentiality of the person who is reporting the violation (and "
"the alleged violator)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:50
msgid "Ensure that the data is stored securely with limited access"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:51
msgid "Make sure that people are aware of reporting mechanisms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:52
msgid "Face to face with staff (Who is the dedicated ombudsperson or -persons?)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:53
msgid "Dedicated email, e.g. to conduct@yourdomain.org"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:54
msgid ""
"Fill out an online form, e.g. [O'Reilly Report "
"CoC](http://www.oreilly.com/conferences/report-code-of-conduct.html)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:55
msgid ""
"Consider how a report against an authority figure would be submitted ‚Äî "
"e.g. if the ombudsperson is the subject of a CoC violation report, who is"
" the report submitted to? (A good reason to have more than one "
"ombudsperson.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:58
msgid "Enforcement"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:60
msgid ""
"Be clear on how long it will take to resolve the situation or take an "
"action on the violation"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:61
msgid ""
"Discuss in advance with the organizing committee what the specific "
"process will be for recording and addressing a CoC violation"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:62
msgid ""
"When possible, have a third party review the violation report (Another "
"good way to handle the challenge of potential reports against authority "
"figures.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/07_code_of_conduct.md:63
msgid ""
"Ensure the person who made the CoC violation report is aware of how it is"
" being handled and when it has been resolved."
msgstr ""

